{"id": "duc04-testb-1:8#24", "contents": "According to Jeffrey Kessler, the chief outside counsel for the union, the proposal includes provisions for some players. The union aims to prevent Chicago from re-signing Michael Jordan and believes the league shares the same sentiment. The proposal is similar to the luxury tax proposed by the union in 1995, but with some key differences. A salary cap credit would be implemented if the league's salary expenditures exceed 63% of revenues, resulting in a reduction of the salary cap the following year."}
